'''Von Babo's law''' (sometimes styled '''Babo's law''') is a [[scientific law]] formulated by German [[chemist]] [[Lambert Heinrich von Babo]]. It states that the [[vapor pressure]] of solution decreases according to the concentration of solute.<ref name="perman1926">Perman, Edgar Philip; Lovett, Trevor. Vapour pressure and heat of dilution of aqueous solutions. ''[[Transactions of the Faraday Society]]'', 1926, 22, 1-19 {{doi|10.1039/TF9262200001}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/oi/authority.20110803095438956|title=Babo's law - Oxford Reference|access-date=2017-12-28}}</ref>

